{[%evp 0,90,38,38,38,25,8,17,31,6,3,-5,28,7,8,8,18,-1,21,-21,34,3,-8,-14,3,4,19,12,7,0,28,-26,-24,-30,-17,-17,-6,-7,8,21,0,13,2,-3,24,-39,-35,-24,-20,-29,-17,-31,-26,-110,-150,-138,-156,-167,-167,-167,-201,-204,-207,-221,-313,-371,-151,-171,-306,-476,-243,-252,-252,-389,-341,-324,-358,-360,-384,-384,-500,-579,-584,-584,-688,-800,-374,-707,-456,-1000,-1158,-1127,-1555] in this game we see the typical c5-c5 advance by black ...while keeping in mind and preventind White's typical b2-b3 reaction!} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 O-O 8. h3 d6 9. c3 Nb8 10. d4 Nbd7 11. Nbd2 c5 {This idea is possible here as well} 12. d5 {In this case, Black didn't commit to Bb7, but White didn't play a4 still} c4 (12... Qc7 13. c4 $1 $14) 13. Bc2 Qc7 $3 {and this is the great move ...preventing b2-b3!} (13... Bb7 $2 14. a4 (14. b3 cxb3 15. axb3 Qc7 16. Bb2 Rfe8 17. b4 Nb6 18. Bb3 Nc4 19. Nxc4 bxc4 20. Ba4 $16) 14... Nc5 15. Nf1 Nfd7 16. Ng3 g6 17. Bh6 Re8 18. Qd2 Nb6 19. a5 Nbd7 $11) (13... Nc5 $6 14. b3 cxb3 15. axb3 Bd7 (15... a5 $5) 16. b4 Na4 17. Bxa4 bxa4 18. c4 $16 Qc7 19. Ba3 $16) 14. Nf1 (14. a4 $2 {Once again this move is not correct} Rb8 $1 (14... Bb7 $2) 15. Nf1 Nc5 16. Ng3 (16. g4 h5 $1 $15 (16... g6 17. Bh6 Rd8 18. Ng3 Bd7 19. axb5 axb5 $11 {[%cal Rb8a8,Rd8b8,Rc7d8]})) 16... Bd7 (16... Bb7 $4)) 14... Nc5 (14... a5 $1 {is another very good option!}) 15. N3h2 (15. b4 cxb3 16. axb3 Bd7 17. N3h2 a5 $1 $15 18. f4 (18. Bd2 Rfc8 19. Qe2 Qb7 20. f4 b4 $15 (20... a4 21. b4 Nb3 $15)) 18... b4 $1 $17 (18... Qb7 19. f5 b4 20. cxb4 (20. c4 a4) 20... axb4 $15) (18... a4 $1 $17 19. b4 Nb3 20. Bxb3 Qxc3 $15)) (15. g4 h5 $15 16. gxh5 Bxh3 (16... g6 $3 $17 17. hxg6 fxg6 18. Bh6 Bxh3 $3 19. Bxf8 Rxf8 20. Ne3 (20. Ng3 Bg4 $19) 20... Ng4 $19 (20... Nh5 $19))) 15... a5 16. a3 (16. a4 bxa4 (16... b4 17. Ng3 b3 18. Bb1 g6 $19 {The b1-bishop and the a1-rook are out of the game forever} 19. Bh6 Bd7 $1 20. Bxf8 Bxf8 21. Ng4 Bxg4 22. hxg4 Bh6 23. Qe2 Ncd7 $19)) 16... Rb8 17. Bd2 Nfd7 $1 {Intending to trasfer the knight to b6 and later a4} 18. Ng3 Qd8 (18... Nb6 19. Rb1 Bh4 $36 20. Nf5 Bxf5 21. exf5 Nxd5 $15) 19. Nf5 Nb6 20. Nxe7+ (20. Qf3 Bxf5 $3 21. Qxf5 (21. exf5 Bg5 $15) 21... g6 22. Qf3 (22. Qg4 h5 23. Qg3 Bh4 24. Qe3 (24. Qf3 Bg5 $15) 24... Nb3 25. Bxb3 cxb3 $17) 22... Bg5 $17) 20... Qxe7 21. Be3 Nba4 22. Rb1 (22. Bxc5 Nxc5 23. Qd2 Qh4 $15 (23... f5)) (22. Bxa4 Nxa4 23. Rb1 f5 $19) 22... f5 $17 23. f3 $2 f4 $19 {Now Black is starting an attack typical for the "Mar del Plata" structure in the KID} 24. Bf2 g5 25. Kf1 Bd7 26. Ke2 b4 27. axb4 axb4 28. Qd2 b3 29. Bd1 Nd3 (29... h5 30. Rg1 h4 $19) 30. Rg1 Bb5 31. Kf1 Ra8 32. g3 Kh8 33. gxf4 gxf4 34. Rg4 Bd7 35. Bh4 Qf7 36. Be2 Nac5 37. Kg2 h5 38. Rg5 Rg8 39. Bxd3 Nxd3 40. Kh1 Rxg5 41. Bxg5 Bxh3 42. Rg1 Rg8 43. Qe2 Kh7 44. Bh4 Rxg1+ 45. Kxg1 Qa7+ {total destruction!} 0-1

