{[%evp 0,72,38,38,38,19,22,26,24,3,27,-13,1,12,35,40,39,2,25,32,26,26,20,17,17,3,-13,-16,-15,-15,-10,-17,-17,-17,0,2,11,10,8,14,-1,-5,3,-18,-10,-43,-55,-57,-43,-25,0,-93,-1,-19,-20,-20,-24,-24,-24,-20,-21,-20,-23,-22,-20,-20,-29,-29,-7,-22,-16,-106,-107,-29993,-29994] A great game by Black in the dxe5 strategy. I only dislike the move 16...Nh5} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 5. c3 Bd7 6. d4 g6 7. O-O Bg7 8. Re1 b5 9. Bb3 Nf6 10. dxe5 (10. d5 Na5 11. Bc2 c6 $1) 10... Nxe5 $1 {Correct move. Black wants to exchange his c6-knight and also free his c7-pawn.} 11. Nxe5 dxe5 12. Nd2 (12. Be3 O-O 13. Nd2 Qe7 14. f3 c5 $11) 12... c5 $1 (12... O-O {It is better to hurry with c7-c5.} 13. Nf3 Re8 14. Be3) 13. Nf3 (13. c4 O-O) 13... c4 $1 14. Bc2 Qc7 $15 15. Qe2 (15. Bd2 O-O 16. Qc1 Rab8 17. Bh6 Bg4 18. Bxg7 Kxg7 19. Qe3 Bxf3 20. Qxf3 a5 $17 {[%cal Rb5b4]}) 15... O-O 16. h3 Nh5 $5 (16... h6 $1 17. Be3 Be6 18. Rad1 a5 19. a3 Kh7 (19... Nd7) 20. Nh2 Rab8 $17) (16... a5 $3 $15) 17. a4 Rab8 18. axb5 axb5 19. Be3 Nf4 20. Bxf4 exf4 21. Red1 Rfe8 22. Nd4 b4 23. Ba4 Bxa4 24. Rxa4 Qc5 25. Qf3 Qe5 26. Rxb4 (26. Nc6 Qb5 $19) 26... Rxb4 27. Nc6 Qxe4 28. Qxe4 Rxe4 29. Nxb4 Re2 30. Rd8+ Bf8 31. Rc8 Rxb2 32. Rxc4 Rb1+ 33. Kh2 Bd6 34. f3 g5 35. Rd4 Bc5 36. Rd5 Bg1+ 0-1

