{in this game, we will see many typical mistakes by Black!! They are leading to a total catastrophe! Try to avoid all these mistakes!!} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O b5 6. Bb3 d6 7. Re1 Be7 $1 8. c3 (8. d4 $6 Nxd4 9. Nxd4 exd4 10. Qxd4 $4 c5 11. Qd1 c4 $19) 8... O-O 9. h3 Na5 10. Bc2 c5 11. d4 cxd4 $6 {This is premature, but let's say it is playable.} (11... Qc7 $1 {is the correct move order}) 12. cxd4 Qc7 13. Nbd2 (13. Nc3 $1 {The knight belongs to "c3" if this is possible.}) 13... Bb7 $2 {another mistake...a big one this time! ...... The bishop has nothing to do on b7 when white can block it with d4-d5 !! ...we should put the bishop on d7!} (13... Bd7 $1 {Is the correct move} 14. Nf1 (14. d5 Rfc8 15. Bd3 Nb7 $1 16. b4 $2 Qc3 $1 $19) 14... Rfe8 $11) 14. d5 $1 Rac8 $6 {this move is tempting, but it s another mistake !!! Now the rook occupies the ONLY good square for the Bb7 and this bishop is trapped forever on the queenside !!} (14... Nc4 $2 15. Nxc4 Qxc4 16. Bd3 Qc7 17. Bd2 $16 {in an open position, white's superior bishops give him a huge advantage} Nd7 18. Rc1 $16) (14... Bc8 $1 {That is the only decent move here. Black should admit his mistake. White is still better, though} 15. Rb1 (15. Nf1 Bd7 16. b3 $14) 15... Bd7 (15... Nb7 16. b4 $3 {x Nb7} a5 17. a3 $16) 16. b3 (16. Bd3) 16... Rac8 17. Bd3 Rfe8 (17... Nb7 18. b4) 18. Nf1 h6 (18... Bf8 19. Bg5 $16) 19. Bd2 Nb7 20. b4 $16) 15. Bd3 Ba8 $2 16. Nf1 Nb7 $2 (16... Nc4 17. Ng3 g6 18. b3 Nb6 19. Bd2) 17. Ng3 $2 (17. b4 $1 $18 {is about +3.20 in the computer's evaluation ! This is not a surprise if we look at the Nb7 and the Ba8 !!!} Qc3 18. Rb1) 17... Rfe8 $2 (17... Nc5 18. Bf1 $16 (18. Nf5 $5)) 18. Nf5 $1 $16 (18. b4 $16) 18... Bf8 19. Bg5 $1 $18 (19. b4 g6 20. Nh6+ Kg7 21. Ng5 Re7 22. Nhxf7 h6 23. Nxh6 $18) 19... Nc5 (19... Nd7 20. b4 $18 Nb6 (20... f6 21. Bd2) 21. Qe2 Nc4 22. a4 {the position is resignable for black} f6 23. Bd2 $18 (23. Bc1) (23. Bh4) 23... Nxd2 24. Qxd2 g6 25. Ne3) 20. Bxf6 Nxd3 21. Qxd3 gxf6 22. Nh2 Kh8 23. Ng4 Qc2 24. Qg3 Bg7 25. Nxe5 {This game shows many typical mistakes by Black. You need to study it carefully and try never to repeat them.} 1-0

