{in this game Magnus Carlsen allowed a Ng4-Nh6+ which is the same idea with a Nf5 move by white..and there is never g6 after that...because this Nh6+ is very strong!} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. d3 d6 7. c3 O-O 8. Nbd2 Re8 9. Re1 b5 10. Bc2 (10. Bb3 Na5 11. Bc2 c5 12. Nf1 h6 $1 13. Ng3 Bf8 {[%cal Rg7g6]} 14. d4 Qc7 (14... cxd4 15. cxd4 Bg4 (15... exd4 16. Nxd4 g6)) 15. d5 g6) 10... Bf8 11. Nf1 g6 12. h3 Bb7 13. Ng3 Nb8 14. d4 Nbd7 15. a4 c5 16. d5 c4 17. Bg5 Bg7 18. Qd2 Rb8 19. Nh2 Bc8 $2 (19... Qc7 $1 20. Ng4 Nxg4 21. hxg4 Nc5 $11) 20. Ng4 Nc5 21. Nh6+ (21. axb5 $2 axb5 (21... Bxg4 $1 22. hxg4 axb5 $11) 22. Nh6+ Bxh6 23. Bxh6 $16) 21... Bxh6 22. Bxh6 bxa4 23. Ra2 a3 24. bxa3 Nfd7 25. f4 a5 26. Rf1 f6 27. f5 Nd3 28. Bxd3 cxd3 29. Qd1 Re7 30. Raf2 Rf7 31. Qxd3 Nc5 32. Qf3 Ba6 33. Qg4 g5 34. h4 Bxf1 35. Rxf1 Qd7 36. hxg5 fxg5 37. Qh5 Kh8 38. f6 Rg8 39. Bg7+ Rfxg7 40. fxg7+ Qxg7 41. Nf5 Qg6 42. Qxg6 Rxg6 43. Ne7 Kg7 (43... Rh6 44. Rf8+ Kg7 45. Rc8 Rf6 46. Nf5+ Kg6 47. Nxd6) 44. Nxg6 Kxg6 45. Rf8 a4 46. c4 h5 47. Kf2 1-0

