{[%evp 0,96,34,34,13,25,25,13,16,7,28,15,15,9,9,9,9,9,16,-10,-9,-49,-22,-22,-34,-47,27,42,31,22,22,24,28,34,40,47,39,18,15,22,24,0,32,-13,-8,-6,9,12,16,-27,-28,-28,-28,-28,-31,-36,-43,-32,-43,-61,-61,-46,-37,-37,-37,-53,-29,-32,-37,-53,-38,-66,-72,-60,-39,-98,-80,-65,-65,-65,-74,-87,-94,-231,-104,-251,-253,-336,-350,-344,-341,-505,-499,-514,-514,-540,-543,-760,-759]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 5. Bxc6+ bxc6 6. d4 exd4 $1 {This is one of the two good options for Black.} ({Obviously,} 6... f6 $1 7. Nc3 Ne7 8. O-O Ng6 {is the alternative direction.}) 7. Qxd4 Nf6 8. Nc3 ({A good reaction to} 8. e5 {is} Nd7 {Later on, Black can proceed with ...Nc5 followed by ...d6-d5.}) 8... Be7 {It's important to remember that when the white queen is on d4, we are not in a hurry to play ...c6-c5. We can always play it.} 9. Bg5 O-O 10. e5 Nd7 $15 {This retreat is a thematic response to the advance e4-e5. Black is now ready to follow with ...Nc6 and ...d6-d5.} ({A good alternative would have been} 10... Ng4 $1 $15 {when Black is again slightly better.}) 11. Bf4 dxe5 {Even though Black managed to win at the end, I don't like this move so much.} ({I would have played} 11... Nc5) ({or} 11... d5 12. O-O Nc5 {In both cases, Black has the advantage.}) 12. Nxe5 Bf6 13. O-O-O Nxe5 14. Bxe5 Qxd4 15. Bxd4 Bg5+ 16. Kb1 Bf5 17. Be5 Rac8 18. f3 Rfe8 19. Rhe1 h5 20. h3 Bh4 21. Re3 f6 22. Bf4 Rxe3 23. Bxe3 Bg3 24. a4 Re8 25. Bg1 Kf7 26. b3 g5 27. a5 g4 28. hxg4 hxg4 29. fxg4 Bxg4 30. Rf1 Kg6 31. Bd4 f5 32. Na4 Rd8 33. Bf2 Be5 34. Be3 Be2 35. Rh1 f4 36. Bc1 Kf5 37. Bb2 Bxb2 38. Kxb2 Rg8 39. Rh2 Bf1 40. Nc5 Rxg2 41. Rh6 Bb5 42. Kc1 f3 43. Rh3 f2 44. Rf3+ Kg4 45. Rf6 f1=Q+ 46. Rxf1 Bxf1 47. c4 Ra2 48. Na4 Bxc4 0-1

