{[%evp 0,95,28,28,22,27,27,28,28,-4,16,16,16,16,16,-6,-8,-12,-3,-5,1,-35,-26,-33,-13,-34,-35,-37,-13,-19,-9,-42,-5,-5,-2,-17,-17,-23,4,-12,-15,-23,-17,-6,-8,-9,-15,-57,-48,-80,-1,9,14,-26,-14,-75,-22,-160,-64,-50,-46,-38,-35,-39,-38,-39,-32,-38,-19,-64,-58,-96,-22,-142,-142,-148,-148,-146,-146,-171,-172,-206,-256,-267,-232,-275,-217,-445,-501,-646,-733,-1099,-888,-886,-786,-1049,-1142,-1208]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 5. Bxc6+ bxc6 6. d4 ({Positionally speaking, the move 6.d4 is almost forced. In case of a passive move such as} 6. d3 {Black is ready to claim central space by means of} c5 {After} 7. O-O {Besides the typical 7...Ne7 followed by either ...Ng6 or ...Nc6, Black can also play} g6 {By now, we all know that g7 is the best square for the bishop in this pawn structure. Let's take a look at how the game might continue. A normal move would be} 8. Bg5 ({Black is quite ready for an open position. The following line is a good example -} 8. c3 Bg7 9. d4 cxd4 10. cxd4 exd4 11. Nxd4 Ne7 12. Nc3 O-O {Black is already better. He can consider ...Bb7 followed by ...Qd7, and ...f7-f5.}) 8... Qd7 9. Nbd2 h6 10. Bh4 Bg7 11. c3 Ne7 12. Re1 O-O 13. Nf1 Nc6 14. Ne3 f5 {Black has a huge advantage in this position. I would even say that his is strategically winning. Obviously, when we have an active play on the kingside, we don't need to spend time on moves such as ...a6-a5.}) 6... exd4 $1 {Play this if you are in the mood for an open game or 6...f6! if you prefer a close game that day!} (6... f6 $1) 7. Nxd4 c5 8. Ne2 Nf6 9. Nbc3 Bb7 10. Ng3 g6 {Black has perfect counterplay with his strong bishops!} 11. Bf4 h5 12. h4 Bg7 13. Qd2 Ng4 {Black plays just line in the previous game.} ({According to the computer, more precise would have been} 13... Qe7 14. O-O-O O-O-O $3 {The point is that} 15. Nd5 Qd7 16. Bg5 {will be answered by} Nxd5 17. exd5 {This move is forced.} ({White cannot just take the exchange since after} 17. Bxd8 $2 Nb6 $1 18. Bg5 Bxb2+ $19 {Black is winning.}) 17... Qa4 18. Kb1 Rde8 $17 {Black has an obvious advantage.}) 14. Bg5 Qd7 15. O-O f6 16. Bf4 Ne5 17. Nd5 O-O 18. Rad1 Kh7 19. f3 a5 20. Ne3 a4 21. Ne2 Bc6 22. Nc3 Rab8 23. Qc1 Qf7 24. Ncd5 Bb5 25. Rf2 Rfe8 26. Kh1 Rb7 27. Rg1 Nc4 28. a3 Nxe3 29. Nxe3 Bd7 30. c3 Rbb8 31. Rd1 Be6 32. Rdd2 Bd7 33. Qd1 f5 34. exf5 Bxf5 35. Nxf5 Qxf5 36. Bg3 Bxc3 37. Rde2 Bd4 38. Rxe8 Rxe8 39. Rf1 Qd7 40. Qc2 Qb5 41. Rb1 Re2 42. Qd1 Rxb2 43. Rxb2 Qxb2 44. Kh2 Qxa3 45. Bf4 Qa1 46. Qe2 Be5 47. g3 Qb2 48. Bd2 0-1

