{[%evp 0,126,28,28,27,28,28,28,39,5,16,16,16,16,22,-8,-5,0,15,-2,-7,-6,23,-9,-7,-33,-37,-36,-33,-44,-47,-33,-29,-51,0,-87,-87,-58,36,41,23,-227,-150,-151,-68,-15,0,-239,-5,3,31,-24,61,-40,34,-110,-5,-7,-4,-33,-2,-36,-47,-72,-19,-56,-59,-72,0,-206,-219,-389,-389,-393,-348,-348,-358,-358,-171,-388,-401,-403,-402,-418,-385,-388,-399,-523,-461,-719,-574,-574,-580,-580,-589,-589,-612,-616,-583,-645,-462,-474,-534,-539,-557,-603,-487,-491,-500,-506,-499,-529,-526,-940,-1002,-1012,-1172,-1208,-1582,-2126,-1283,-2024,-1295,-29993,-29994,-29995,-29992,-29993,-29990]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 5. Bxc6+ bxc6 6. d4 exd4 7. Nxd4 c5 8. Nf3 {So far we have been mainly studying 8.Ne2 but the exact move order does not make too much of a difference. In any case, we do not need theory to play this position.} g6 9. O-O ({In case of} 9. Bg5 {I would prefer} Qd7 ({But} 9... f6 {is playable as well.})) 9... Bg7 10. Nc3 Ne7 {When possible, try to develop the knight on e7.} 11. Bg5 h6 {This should be your automatic reaction to Bg5. Black immediately wants to clarify the position of White's dark-squared bishop. White's immediate threat was Nd5.} 12. Be3 O-O 13. Qd2 Kh7 14. Rfe1 {This harmless move shows that White does not have a plan in this position.} Rb8 $17 {This continuation is enough for an obvious advantage.} ({Probably, I would have even played} 14... Bg4 {when it's not so easy for White to avoid structural damages.}) 15. Rab1 Bb7 16. Rbd1 f5 17. e5 Bxf3 18. gxf3 Bxe5 19. Bxh6 Nc6 20. Bf4 Qh4 21. Bg3 Qf6 22. Nd5 Qf7 23. f4 Bg7 24. c3 Rbe8 25. Qd3 Nd8 26. Ne3 Re4 27. Nc2 c4 28. Qd2 Ne6 29. f3 Rxe1+ 30. Rxe1 Nc5 31. Nd4 Nd3 32. Re2 Re8 33. b3 c5 34. Nc2 Bxc3 35. Qxc3 Rxe2 36. bxc4 Nc1 37. Ne3 Nxa2 38. Qd3 Rb2 39. Nd5 Nc1 40. Qe3 Ne2+ 41. Kf1 Nd4 42. Bh4 Rxh2 43. Bg3 Re2 44. Qg1 Qb7 45. Bf2 Qb1+ 46. Kg2 Qxg1+ 47. Kxg1 Nxf3+ 48. Kf1 Rc2 49. Nf6+ Kg7 50. Ne8+ Kf7 51. Nxd6+ Ke6 52. Nb7 Rxc4 53. Nxc5+ Kd5 54. Nxa6 Rxf4 55. Ke2 Nd4+ 56. Ke3 Rf3+ 57. Kd2 Rxf2+ 58. Ke1 Re2+ 59. Kf1 Rb2 60. Nc7+ Ke4 61. Ne8 Kf3 62. Ke1 Re2+ 63. Kd1 Rxe8 0-1

