{Another endgame variation perfectly fine for Black!} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 5. O-O Bd7 6. d4 Nf6 7. dxe5 {Not very ambtious! Now both 7... Nxe5 and 7...de5 are very good!} Nxe5 $1 8. Bxd7+ Qxd7 9. Nxe5 dxe5 10. Qxd7+ Kxd7 $132 11. Nc3 $2 {One mistake and Black is better!} (11. f3 Bc5+ 12. Kh1 Ke6 $132) 11... Bb4 $1 $15 {A very strong move. We develop the bishop with a tempo and want to spoil White's pawn structure.} 12. Nd5 (12. Bd2 Ke6 $17 {[%cal Gh8d8]}) ({It goes without saying that after} 12. f3 {Black will immediately play} Bxc3 13. bxc3 Ke6 $17 {[%cal Gf6e8,Ge8d6,Gd6c4] with a huge advantage. Later on, we will maneuver the knight all the way to c4.}) 12... Nxd5 13. exd5 Rad8 (13... f5 $17) (13... Kd6 14. c4 Bc5 15. Bd2 b5 16. b4 Bd4 17. c5+ Kxd5 $17) 14. Be3 f5 15. f3 Rhe8 16. a3 Bf8 17. Bg5 Be7 18. Bxe7 Kxe7 19. Rad1 Rd6 20. Rfe1 Kf6 21. c4 Red8 22. Rc1 c6 23. dxc6 Rxc6 24. Kf2 Rd2+ 25. Re2 Rd4 26. Rec2 e4 27. b4 Ke5 28. b5 Rc5 29. a4 g5 30. Ke2 exf3+ 31. Kxf3 g4+ 32. Kf2 f4 33. Re1+ Re4 34. Rec1 h5 35. Rc3 h4 36. R1c2 Kd4 37. Rc1 Re3 38. R3c2 g3+ 39. hxg3 hxg3+ 40. Kf1 Rh5 41. Rd1+ Rd3 42. Ke2 Rxd1 (42... f3+ 43. gxf3 Rh2+ 44. Ke1 Rxc2) 43. Kxd1 Rh2 44. c5 f3 45. c6 bxc6 46. bxc6 fxg2 47. Rxg2 Rxg2 48. c7 Rg1+ (48... Kd3 49. Ke1 Rc2 (49... Rg1#)) 49. Kd2 g2 50. c8=Q Rd1+ 51. Kxd1 g1=Q+ 52. Kd2 Qe3+ 53. Kc2 Qd3+ 54. Kb2 Qd2+ 55. Kb3 Qd3+ 56. Kb4 Qb1+ 57. Ka5 Qb5+ 0-1

