1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 ({The following classical game by Alekhine is the reason why I chose the wrong move order.} 4... Nf6 5. O-O d6 6. c3 Bd7 7. Re1 Be7 8. d4 O-O 9. Nbd2 Be8 $1 {Black is freeing the d7-square for the knight. Also, this move is connected with a very precise calculation.} 10. Bxc6 Bxc6 11. dxe5 dxe5 12. Nxe5 Bxe4 13. Nxe4 Qxd1 14. Nxf6+ ({After} 14. Rxd1 Nxe4 15. f3 Nd6 {Black keeps an advantage in view of his bishop pair.}) 14... gxf6 $3 15. Rxd1 fxe5 16. Bh6 Rfd8 {This instructive endgame was analyzed in many books. I really suggest that you follow this game until the end.} 17. Kf1 f5 18. Rxd8+ (18. g3 Kf7 19. Be3 Ke6 20. Ke2 h5 21. Rxd8 Rxd8 22. Rd1 Rg8 $15 (22... Kf7 23. Ke1 Rc8 24. Ke2 Ke6 $15)) 18... Rxd8 19. g3 Kf7 20. Be3 h5 21. Ke2 Ke6 22. Rd1 Rg8 23. f3 (23. h4 Rg4) 23... h4 24. Bf2 hxg3 25. hxg3 Rh8 26. Bg1 Bd6 27. Kf1 Rg8 28. Bf2 b5 $3 29. b3 (29. a4 bxa4 30. Ra1 Rb8 31. Ra2 (31. Rxa4 Rxb2 32. Rxa6 Rc2 (32... Kd5)) 31... a5 (31... a3 32. b4 a5 33. bxa5 Ra8 $17) 32. Ke2 a3 33. bxa3 a4 $17 (33... Rb3)) 29... a5 30. Kg2 (30. a4 bxa4 31. bxa4 Rb8) 30... a4 $3 31. Rd2 (31. b4 Rc8 $3 32. Bc5 Ra8 $3 33. Kf1 Ra6 34. Ke2 (34. Bxd6 cxd6) 34... Bxc5 $19 (34... Rc6 $19)) (31. bxa4 bxa4 32. Rb1 Kd5 33. Rb5+ Kc4 34. Ra5 a3 35. Be1 Rb8 $19) 31... axb3 32. axb3 Ra8 33. c4 Ra3 34. c5 Be7 35. Rb2 b4 $1 36. g4 f4 $3 37. Kf1 Ra1+ 38. Ke2 Rc1 39. Ra2 Rc3 40. Ra7 Kd7 41. Rb7 Rxb3 42. Rb8 Rb2+ 43. Kf1 b3 44. Kg1 Kc6 45. Kf1 Kd5 $3 46. Rb7 (46. Re8 Rxf2+ 47. Kxf2 Bxc5+ 48. Ke2 b2 49. Rb8 Bb6 $19) 46... e4 $3 47. fxe4+ Kxe4 48. Rxc7 Kf3 49. Rxe7 (49. Be1 Rh2 50. Kg1 b2 51. Rb7 Rc2 52. g5 Bxc5+ (52... Rc1) 53. Kf1 Rh2 54. Rb3+ Be3 $19) 49... Rxf2+ 50. Ke1 b2 51. Rb7 Rc2 52. c6 Kg3 53. c7 f3 54. Kd1 Rxc7 55. Rxb2 f2 {Znosko-Borovsky - Alekhne 1933 Paris  (0-1)}) 5. O-O Bd7 6. d4 Nf6 $1 {Pay attention to this important move.} ({The immediate} 6... b5 $6 {allows White to overtake the initiative after} 7. Bb3 Nxd4 8. Nxd4 exd4 9. c3 $36) 7. Re1 $6 {This move is not precise.} ({Better would have been} 7. d5 Ne7 8. Bxd7+ Qxd7 (8... Nxd7 {is possible as well.}) 9. Re1 Ng6 {Black will start gradually preparing the advance ...f7-f5. This kind of structure will be extensively discussed in the next lecture.} ({Another possibility is} 9... g6)) 7... Be7 $2 {And here, due to lack of practice, I forgot my analysis and played this mistake. Black should play 7... b5! with a perfect game!} (7... b5 8. dxe5 {White should already go for this symmetrical position.} ({In case of} 8. Bb3 Nxd4 9. Nxd4 exd4 10. e5 dxe5 11. Rxe5+ Be7 {White cannot take on d4 because of ...c7-c5 followed by ...c5-c4. Also, White has serious problems with the development of his queenside. Black is simply better.}) 8... dxe5 9. Bb3 Bb4 {I like this little move which spoils White's coordination. The idea is to provoke c2-c3 so that the c3-square will no longer be available for the knight.} (9... Bc5) (9... Be7) 10. c3 Bd6 $132) 8. c3 O-O 9. Nbd2 $1 b5 10. Bc2 Re8 11. d5 $1 $16 (11. Nf1 $2 Bf8 $132 (11... h6 12. d5 Na5 13. b3 (13. b4 Nc4) 13... c6 $132) 12. d5 Ne7 $132) (11. h3 $2 Bf8) 11... Na5 (11... Nb8 12. a4) 12. b4 Nb7 13. Nf1 (13. a4) 13... Bf8 14. Ng3 $5 (14. Bg5 $1 h6 15. Bh4 Be7 16. a4 Nh7 17. Bxe7) 14... g6 15. a4 h6 16. h4 $5 (16. axb5 $5) 16... Bg7 17. Qe2 $16 c6 18. dxc6 Bxc6 19. h5 Qc7 (19... Nxh5 20. Nxh5 gxh5 21. axb5 axb5 22. Rxa8 Qxa8 23. Nh4) (19... bxa4 $4 20. hxg6 fxg6 21. Qc4+) 20. hxg6 $6 (20. axb5 Bxb5) (20. Nh4 $1 Kh7 21. Bb3 $1 $18 Rf8 (21... Nd8 22. Bxf7) (21... g5 22. Nhf5 Bf8) (21... d5 22. hxg6+ fxg6 23. exd5 Bxd5 (23... Nxd5 24. Nxg6 Nf4 25. Bxf4 exf4 26. Qd3)) 22. Bxf7) 20... fxg6 21. Nh4 Kh7 22. Qf3 $2 (22. f4 bxa4 $1 23. f5 g5 24. Ng6 Bb5 25. Qf3 a5 $17 26. Ba3 axb4 (26... Rec8 $19) 27. Bxb4 Nc5 28. Bxc5 Qxc5+ 29. Kh2 a3 30. Nh5) (22. Bd2 bxa4 23. Bxa4 Nd8 24. Bxc6 Qxc6 25. Nf3 Ne6) 22... bxa4 $3 $132 23. Bb1 (23. Bxa4 Bxa4 24. Rxa4 a5 (24... Nd8 25. Qd3 Ne6 26. Nf3 Qc6 (26... Rec8 27. Bd2 Qc6 28. Rea1) 27. Ra5 Rec8 (27... Nf4)) (24... d5 $3 25. exd5 Nd6 $132)) 23... Bd7 $15 24. Ba2 Rf8 $1 $15 25. Nxg6 $5 Kxg6 26. Nf5 Kh7 27. Nxg7 (27. Qg3 Bxf5 28. exf5 Nd8 29. Qg6+ Kh8 30. Bxh6 Bxh6 31. Qxh6+ Nh7 32. Bd5 Rc8 (32... Ra7) 33. Rxa4 Nf7) 27... Kxg7 28. Qg3+ Kh7 29. Qh4 Ng4 30. Bd5 $2 (30. f3 $4 Qb6+ 31. Kf1 Rac8) (30. Qe7+ Kh8 31. Be6 Qxc3 $15 (31... Qb6 32. Be3 Nxe3 33. Rxe3 $3 Bxe6 34. Qxe6 Kh7 35. Qe7+ Kh8 36. Qe6 $11)) 30... Rab8 $1 31. f3 Qb6+ 32. Kf1 Qd8 $1 33. Qh5 Qe8 $1 34. Qh4 Qg6 $1 $19 35. Ke2 Nf6 36. Rh1 h5 $5 37. Bg5 Kg7 38. Rad1 (38. g4 Nxd5 39. exd5 Rbc8 40. gxh5 Qc2+ 41. Bd2) 38... Nxd5 39. Rxd5 a3 $3 40. Rd2 (40. Ra1 Be6 41. Rd2 a2) 40... Be6 41. g4 a2 $3 42. Ke3 (42. gxh5 Qf7 43. Qg3 Kh7) 42... Rbc8 $1 43. Rg2 Qf7 44. f4 Rxc3+ 45. Kd2 Rfc8 46. Bh6+ Kh7 (46... Kxh6 $5 $19) 0-1

