{[%evp 0,76,61,17,26,18,13,25,25,3,38,21,22,-21,73,41,40,5,28,30,36,23,23,2,-8,-17,-11,-7,-21,10,-15,-9,-3,-5,34,17,23,1,16,-36,6,-11,-35,-17,-41,-91,-41,-99,-60,-58,3,-65,-77,-47,-81,-69,-89,-80,-101,-101,-103,-168,-60,-82,-158,-168,-250,-250,-147,-768,-1005,-1005,-1195,-1266,-1571,-1878,-1951,-29993,-29994]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 5. O-O Bd7 6. c3 g6 7. d4 Bg7 8. d5 Nce7 9. Bxd7+ {Of course, this move should be played immediately.} ({A move such as} 9. h3 $6 {will be answered by} b5 $1 {when Black is already better.}) 9... Qxd7 10. c4 h6 11. Nc3 f5 12. b4 ({As we know, after} 12. exf5 gxf5 13. Nh4 {Black has the wonderful} Bf6 $3 {For instance, the endgame arising after} 14. Qh5+ Kf8 15. Re1 Qe8 16. Qxe8+ Rxe8 17. Nf3 Ng6 $17 {is clearly in Black's favour.}) 12... Nf6 13. Nd2 O-O 14. f3 c6 $1 {Always consider this move when you see that the c3-knight is unstable. Sometimes, Black can use the c-file by means of ...Rac8 followed by ...cxd5.} ({Dubious is} 14... f4 $6 {when after} 15. c5 g5 16. Nc4 {White manages to develop his typical King's Indian play.}) 15. Bb2 Rac8 16. Qe2 {White wants to connect the rooks as soon as possible.} ({In case of} 16. dxc6 {I prefer} Nxc6 {The knight is heading for the weak d4-square.} ({Of course,} 16... bxc6 {is possible as well.}) 17. Nd5 (17. a3 Nd4) 17... Nxd5 18. cxd5 Nd4 (18... Nxb4) 19. Bxd4 exd4 20. exf5 Qxf5 21. Ne4 Qxd5 {Black is better.}) ({In response to} 16. Rc1 {an important idea is} h5 $3 {[%cal Gg7h6] Whenever the white bishop is not on the diagonal c1-h6, it makes a lot of sense to play ...h6-h5 followed by ...Bh6. Remember this idea! A possible continuation would be} 17. Rc2 Bh6 18. Qe2 h4 19. Qf2 cxd5 (19... Bg5 $19) 20. cxd5 Bg5 $19 {Black enjoys an overwhelming activity.}) 16... Nh5 $5 ({In my opinion. Black should have started with} 16... cxd5 $1 {clarifying the structure in the centre. As we know, after} 17. cxd5 {Black's typical reaction would be} h5 18. Nc4 Qc7 19. Ne3 Bh6 $19 {Again, Black has a winning advantage. White cannot keep intact his overextended position.}) 17. g3 Nf6 18. Rac1 h5 $1 19. Kg2 cxd5 20. Nxd5 Nexd5 $1 (20... Nfxd5 $2 21. cxd5) 21. exd5 (21. cxd5 Bh6 $19) 21... b5 $1 $19 22. Qd3 Qb7 23. a4 bxc4 24. Nxc4 Qxd5 25. Qe2 Qe6 26. Rfd1 Rfd8 27. Nb6 Rxc1 28. Rxc1 d5 29. a5 e4 30. Rd1 h4 31. fxe4 fxe4 32. gxh4 Nh5 33. Bc1 d4 34. Qc2 Qg4+ 35. Kh1 Qf3+ 36. Kg1 d3 37. Qb3+ Kh7 38. h3 Bd4+ 0-1

