{a fine example of the Bg5 Spanish Smyslov line.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 g6 5. O-O Bg7 6. c3 d6 7. d4 Bd7 8. Re1 b5 9. Bb3 Nf6 10. Bg5 {the Bg5 system in my view is not dangerous at all!} h6 11. Bxf6 $6 Bxf6 12. Nbd2 O-O 13. Bd5 Rb8 $1 (13... Rc8 $1 14. Bxc6 (14. h3 exd4 15. Bxc6 Bxc6 16. cxd4 Re8 17. d5 (17. e5 Bg7 18. Rc1 Bd5 19. exd6 cxd6 $15) (17. Rc1 Bb7 18. b3 c5 $15) 17... Bb7 18. Rb1 c6 19. dxc6 Rxc6 $132) 14... Bxc6 15. h3 exd4 16. cxd4 Re8 17. Rc1 Bb7 18. d5 c6 $15) 14. Bxc6 (14. Nf1 Ne7 15. Bb3 c5 16. d5 c4 17. Bc2 Kg7 $1 18. Ng3 Ng8 19. Qd2 Qc8 20. h3 Bd8 21. Rad1 Bb6 22. Kh1 Nf6 $15) 14... Bxc6 15. Nb3 Qe7 $15 (15... exd4 $1 $17 {opening up the center when you have the pair of bishops makes a lot of sense} 16. Nbxd4 (16. cxd4 Re8 17. d5 Bd7 (17... Ba8 18. Nbd4 c5 19. dxc6 Rc8 20. Rc1 Qb6 21. Qd2 $11)) 16... Bb7 $15) 16. Qe2 (16. d5 Bd7 17. Na5 Bg7 $15 (17... Rb6)) 16... Rfe8 (16... exd4 $3 $17 17. cxd4 (17. Nbxd4 Bb7 18. e5 Bg7 $17 19. exd6 Qxd6 20. Rad1 Rfe8 (20... Qb6 $17) 21. Qxe8+ Rxe8 22. Rxe8+ Kh7 $17) 17... Rfe8 18. Nbd2 (18. Nfd2 Ba8 19. Rac1 c5 $17 (19... Rbc8)) 18... Bb7 (18... b4 19. Rac1 Bb5 20. Qe3 Bg7 $15) 19. Rac1 c5 $19) 17. d5 Bd7 18. c4 Bg7 (18... c5 $3 19. dxc6 (19. Na5 Qd8 20. Nc6 Bxc6 21. dxc6 Qb6 22. b3 Qxc6 23. Rad1 Be7 24. Nd2 Bd8 $17) 19... Bxc6 20. Rac1 bxc4 21. Qxc4 Bb5 22. Qd5 Qe6 $15) (18... c6 $1 $15) 19. Rac1 c5 $1 20. dxc6 Bxc6 21. c5 d5 22. exd5 (22. Na5 Ba8 23. c6 d4 (23... Qb4 24. exd5) 24. Rc2 Rbc8 $17) 22... Bxd5 23. Red1 Bc4 24. Qe3 Rbc8 $6 (24... e4 $3 25. Nfd4 (25. Nfd2 Bd3 $19 (25... Rbd8 $19)) 25... Rbc8 $17) 25. Nfd2 $3 Bxb3 26. Nxb3 e4 27. Rc2 Red8 28. Rxd8+ Rxd8 29. g3 Qe5 $2 30. c6 $16 Rc8 31. Qd2 Bf6 32. Na5 Bg5 33. Qe2 $2 Qd5 34. b4 Qd3 (34... e3 $3 35. fxe3 (35. f4 Bf6 $19) 35... Bxe3+ 36. Qxe3 Qd1+ $19) 35. Kf1 Qd4 (35... Be7 $1) 36. a3 Bd8 37. Nb3 Qd5 38. Nc5 $2 Qxc6 39. Ra2 Bb6 40. Nxe4 f5 41. Rc2 Qxc2 42. Nf6+ Kf7 {White Resigned} 0-1

