{[%evp 0,74,22,33,31,31,23,29,29,-10,32,0,9,9,45,45,45,30,39,41,84,71,77,57,85,61,125,68,65,76,67,29,53,23,51,30,4,-11,27,-9,-8,-6,-8,-8,-17,-118,-132,-116,-115,-83,-84,-175,-139,-148,-125,-154,-166,-161,-176,-133,-180,-160,-148,-220,-265,-279,-215,-234,-211,-228,-249,-235,-227,-235,-218,-209,-213]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 d6 5. c3 Bd7 6. d4 g6 7. O-O Bg7 8. Be3 Nf6 9. Nbd2 Ng4 $1 {This is a very active continuation! Black has a very good game practically although sometimes the computer may disagree.} 10. Bg5 f6 11. Bh4 Qe7 $5 (11... g5 $1 12. Bg3 h5 13. h4 Qe7 $132) 12. Re1 (12. h3 Nh6 13. Re1 Nf7 14. Nf1 Bh6 15. Ne3 Bxe3 16. Rxe3 g5 17. Bg3 h5 $132) 12... h5 13. h3 Nh6 14. Bg3 g5 15. Nf1 O-O-O 16. Ne3 Qf7 (16... Qe8 $3 $36 17. b4 g4 18. hxg4 hxg4 19. Nh4 f5 20. exf5 Qh5) 17. d5 $2 (17. b4 $36) 17... Ne7 18. c4 g4 19. Bxd7+ Rxd7 20. hxg4 hxg4 21. Nh4 Qh5 22. Kf1 f5 23. Nhxf5 Nexf5 24. exf5 Nxf5 25. Nxf5 Qxf5 26. Qb1 e4 27. Ke2 Be5 28. Bxe5 Qxe5 29. Qc2 g3 30. fxg3 Rg7 31. Kd1 Rxg3 32. Qxe4 Qxe4 33. Rxe4 Rxg2 34. Rc1 Rxb2 35. a4 Rh1+ 36. Re1 Rxe1+ 37. Kxe1 Ra2 0-1

