{[%evp 0,66,25,25,25,25,33,28,27,27,27,23,27,43,24,24,24,24,27,27,20,20,17,17,2,-3,9,1,18,0,0,0,49,33,49,0,71,0,37,37,106,87,190,198,186,186,198,186,186,186,186,178,186,164,186,186,186,-121,-121,-509,-514,-549,-565,-556,-416,-677,-696,-1236,-1167]} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Bxc6 dxc6 5. O-O (5. d4 $6 {check the theoretical file} exd4 6. Qxd4 Qxd4 7. Nxd4 Bd7 (7... c5 {An example of why black should not play c5 so fast. As we mentioned, this move makes the d5 square weak} 8. Ne2 Bd7 9. Nbc3 O-O-O 10. Bf4 Ne7 11. O-O-O Ng6 12. Bg3 Bc6 (12... Be7 13. Nd5) (12... c6 13. Na4) 13. Rxd8+ Kxd8 14. Rd1+ Kc8 15. Nd5 Bxd5 16. Rxd5 Be7 17. f3 Rd8 18. Rxd8+ Kxd8 19. Nc3) 8. Be3 O-O-O (8... Nf6 9. f3 {Misplaced knight}) 9. Nc3 Ne7 10. O-O-O Ng6 11. f3 Bb4 12. Nce2 Rhe8 13. c3 Bf8 14. Rhe1 c5 15. Nc2 b6 16. Nf4 Nxf4 17. Bxf4 Be6 $15) (5. Nxe5 Qd4 6. Nf3 Qxe4+ 7. Qe2 Qxe2+ 8. Kxe2 $15) (5. h3 Ne7 {check the theoretical file} 6. O-O Ng6 7. d3 (7. d4 exd4 8. Qxd4 Qxd4 9. Nxd4 Bd7) 7... c5) 5... Bd6 6. d4 (6. Nc3 c5 7. d3 Ne7 $15 {Controling the center and preparing the typical idea Ng6}) 6... exd4 7. Qxd4 (7. Nxd4 Ne7 8. Nc3 O-O 9. Be3 $6 (9. Re1 Ng6 10. Be3 Qf6 $15 (10... Re8)) (9. f4 Re8 (9... Ng6 10. Be3) (9... f5 10. e5 Bc5 11. Be3 Bxd4 12. Bxd4 Be6 (12... b6 $1 13. Be3 Be6 14. a3 c5) 13. Bc5 $1) 10. Kh1 Bb4 $15) 9... f5 $1 10. exf5 Nxf5 11. Nxf5 Bxf5 $15) 7... f6 8. Be3 Ne7 9. Nbd2 (9. Re1 Ng6 10. Nc3 O-O 11. Rad1 Qe7 12. h3 Be6 $15) 9... Be6 $1 10. Rfd1 {Check the theoretical file. We always give the light square bishop for the night! The bishop on d6 is very powerful and solid, and we want to keep it} Ng6 11. Qc3 (11. Nc4 Bxc4 12. Qxc4 Qe7 $1 13. Qd4 (13. Rd2 O-O-O $15 14. Rad1 Rhe8 15. Rd4 c5 16. R4d2 b5 17. Qf1 Qxe4 $17) (13. Nd4 Qxe4 14. Re1 O-O-O $17) (13. Nd2 O-O-O 14. Qe2 h5 $15) 13... c5 $15 14. Qa4+ b5 15. Qa5 O-O 16. Qc3 Rfe8 $15 17. a4 Rab8 18. axb5 axb5 $15 19. Re1 h6 $3 20. h3 Kh7 $17) 11... Qe7 $1 12. a3 (12. Nc4 $6 Bxc4 13. Qxc4 O-O-O $15 14. c3 Rhe8 15. Nd2 h5 $17 (15... Bf4 $15) (15... Ne5 16. Qe2 Qe6 17. h3 g5 $15) 16. b4 Kb8 17. a4 Ne5 18. Qe2 Ng4 $17) (12. Nd4 O-O-O 13. Nxc6 (13. Nxe6 Qxe6 14. Qb3 Qe5 15. g3 Rhe8 $15) 13... bxc6 14. Qxc6 Qe8 15. Qxa6+ Kd7 $17) 12... O-O-O 13. Nd4 Rhe8 (13... Bd7 $1 {A better option} 14. Nc4 (14. Nf5 Bxf5 15. exf5 Nh4 $17) (14. f3 Qe5 $15) 14... Qxe4 15. Nxd6+ cxd6 16. Nf3 Bf5 $15) (13... Nf4 $1 $15 {That is also a better option than what has been played in the game} 14. g3 (14. Nxc6 Ne2+ 15. Kf1 Nxc3 16. Nxe7+ Bxe7 17. bxc3 Rd6 $15 18. f3 Rhd8 19. Ke2 f5 20. Bd4 g6 $15) 14... c5 $17) 14. Nxc6 (14. Nxe6 Qxe6 15. f3 Be5 16. Qc4 Bxb2 $19) 14... bxc6 15. Qxc6 Ne5 $6 (15... Qf7 {not enough compensation for white}) (15... Bf7 {not enough compensation for white}) 16. Qxa6+ Kd7 17. Qa4+ Kc8 18. c4 c5 19. Nb3 Nxc4 20. Bxc5 Bxc5 21. Qc6+ Qc7 22. Qa8+ Qb8 23. Qc6+ Qc7 24. Qa8+ Qb8 25. Qc6+ Qc7 26. Qa8+ Qb8 27. Qc6+ Qc7 28. Rxd8+ Kxd8 29. Rd1+ Bd6 30. Qa6 Ke7 31. Nd4 Qb6 32. Qa4 Nxb2 33. Nc6+ Kf7 0-1

