1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d4 {We are not afraid of this move. Such early ways to refute the Spanish have been refuted themselves.} exd4 6. O-O (6. e5 Ne4 7. Nxd4 Nc5 8. Nxc6 (8. Bxc6 dxc6 $15 {This differs greatly from the Spanish exchange we have examined so far because White's pawn is already on e5. This fact makes the pawn very weak, and it also weakens the light squares.}) 8... dxc6 9. Qxd8+ Kxd8 10. Bg5+ Be7 (10... Ke8 {We want to keep the bishop pair.} 11. Bb3 Nxb3 12. axb3 h6 13. Bh4 Bf5 14. c3 g5 15. Bg3 Be7 16. Nd2 Rd8 17. Nf3 c5 18. O-O Kd7 19. Rad1+ Kc8 $19) 11. Bxe7+ Kxe7 12. Bb3 Nxb3 13. axb3 Bf5 14. c3 Rhd8 $17 (14... a5 $17 {Also a really nice move that fixes the structure.})) 6... Be7 {The threat is to take on e4.} 7. e5 Ne4 8. Re1 $6 (8. Nxd4 Nc5 (8... Nxe5 9. Qe2 $18) (8... O-O {A good alternative. The idea is again to play Nc5 later on.}) 9. Nf5 $5 O-O $1 10. Qg4 g6 11. Nxe7+ Qxe7 12. Bxc6 dxc6 $132 {All these moves are more or less forced. Black has a good game.}) 8... Nc5 9. Bxc6 dxc6 10. Nxd4 (10. Qxd4 Qxd4 11. Nxd4 Ne6 12. Nf5 (12. Nxe6 Bxe6 $17 {Horrible endgame for White. The pawn on e5 makes White's position very weak because all the light squares are weak.}) 12... Bf8 {Of course, it is very important to keep the bishop pair.} 13. Nc3 h5 14. Bd2 g6 15. Ng3 Bg7 $15) 10... O-O 11. Nc3 Ne6 $6 (11... f5 $3 {Amazingly strong positional move by Black. We let White have a passed pawn, but our idea is to blockade it.} 12. exf6 (12. e6 {This will only lead to White losing the pawn on e6.} Bf6 13. Be3 (13. Nxf5 Bxe6 $15) 13... Nxe6 14. Nxe6 Bxe6 $17) 12... Bxf6 13. Be3 Ne6 14. Nxe6 Bxe6 15. Bc5 Re8 $15) 12. Nf5 Bg5 13. Qg4 Bxc1 14. Raxc1 Qg5 15. Qxg5 Nxg5 16. Ng3 $2 Ne6 17. Rcd1 b6 18. Nce4 Bb7 19. Rd7 c5 $1 20. Red1 Bc6 21. R7d2 Rfd8 22. Rxd8+ Rxd8 23. Rxd8+ Nxd8 $15 {Black is better here because the knight is returning to e6 and White has vulnerable pawns.} 24. Kf1 Ne6 25. Ke2 Nf4+ 26. Kf3 Ng6 27. Nf5 Kf8 28. Ke3 Nxe5 29. Kf4 f6 30. f3 a5 31. b3 c4 32. Nd4 Bd7 33. Ke3 c5 34. Ne2 cxb3 35. cxb3 Ke7 36. h3 a4 37. f4 axb3 38. axb3 Nc6 39. Nd2 Be6 40. g4 Na5 41. Nc1 Kd6 42. f5 Bd5 43. h4 b5 44. Kd3 Nxb3 45. Ncxb3 Bxb3 46. Ne4+ Kd5 47. Nc3+ Kc6 48. g5 Bd5 49. g6 h6 50. Nd1 Kd6 51. Ne3 Ke5 52. Ke2 b4 53. h5 c4 54. Kd2 c3+ 55. Ke2 b3 56. Kd3 b2 57. Ng4+ Kf4 58. Nxf6 b1=Q+ {#R} 0-1

[Event "Bundesliga 2019-20"]
[Site "Kiel GER"]
[Date "2020.02.09"]
