{[%evp 0,62,34,34,5,13,13,13,16,2,2,-4,1,-44,0,-31,14,21,24,14,15,-10,-18,-35,-2,-30,19,7,74,7,-14,-37,-63,-62,-72,-67,-82,-72,-67,-113,-106,-92,-92,-116,-96,-83,-100,-87,-88,-104,-151,-145,-154,-163,-148,-149,-138,-147,-131,-183,-186,-195,-194,-214,-214] An amazing performance by black in the 5.d3 variation.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 d6 6. c3 g6 7. d4 $6 {a little bit slow !} exd4 $3 {A wonderful reaction that shocked me when I first saw this game. Black has a very good version of the Smyslov Spanish anyway after 7...Bd7!? but 7...exd4!! is much better. Black is trying to make use of the extra tempo for fast counter-play.} (7... Bd7 $1 8. O-O Bg7 9. Re1 b5 10. Bc2 O-O {Because of the closed nature of this system White is not worried.}) 8. cxd4 (8. Nxd4 Bd7 9. O-O Bg7 10. Re1 O-O $132 11. Nxc6 Bxc6 12. Bxc6 bxc6 13. Nd2 Re8 14. f3 d5 15. e5 Nh5 $17) 8... b5 9. Bb3 Bg7 10. h3 $6 (10. O-O O-O 11. Re1 Bg4 12. Be3 Na5 13. Bc2 Nc4 14. Bc1 c5 15. h3 Bxf3 16. Qxf3 cxd4 $19 {Total disaster for White.}) 10... O-O 11. O-O Na5 $5 12. Bc2 c5 $5 13. Nc3 $6 (13. d5 Nc4 $1 14. Re1 Re8 15. Nc3 Nd7 $15 16. Bd3 Nce5 17. Nxe5 Nxe5 18. Bf1 f5 $15) (13. dxc5 dxc5 $15 14. Nc3 Bb7 $17) 13... cxd4 $1 $17 {A delayed double capture is still good enough for a big advantage for Black.} 14. Nxd4 Bb7 $1 15. a3 $6 Re8 $1 $17 16. Re1 Rc8 $1 17. Nf3 (17. Nce2 Nxe4 $19) (17. Rb1 d5 18. e5 Ne4 19. Nxe4 dxe4 20. Bxe4 Bxe4 21. Rxe4 Rxe5 22. Rxe5 Bxe5 23. Be3 Nc4 24. b3 Nxe3 25. fxe3 Qf6 $17) 17... Nc4 $1 (17... d5 $1 18. e5 Nd7 19. Bf4 Nc4 $17 20. Nxd5 Ndxe5 $17) 18. Nd2 Nb6 $1 19. Nf1 d5 $1 20. e5 Ne4 $1 21. Bxe4 dxe4 22. Qxd8 Rcxd8 23. Bg5 Rc8 24. Ng3 (24. Nxe4 Bxe4 25. Rxe4 Rxe5 26. Rxe5 Bxe5 27. Rb1 Nc4 28. b3 Nxa3 $19) 24... Rxe5 25. Ncxe4 Bxe4 26. Bf4 Re6 27. Rxe4 Rxe4 28. Nxe4 Bxb2 29. Re1 Bxa3 $3 30. Nf6+ Kh8 31. Ra1 Nc4 {a flawless game!!} 0-1

