1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 d6 6. c4 {Playable and very decent move. White's idea is to play moves like h3, Be3, and sometimes fast Nc3 - d5 idea.} Bg4 $1 {Simple and good.} (6... g6 {Good move, there is a lot of theory but Black can play it.} 7. Nc3 Bg7 8. Nd5 $11) 7. Be3 (7. h3 Bxf3 8. Qxf3 Nd7 {[%cal Yc6d4]} 9. Bxc6 bxc6 10. O-O Nc5 11. Nc3 Ne6 12. Be3 {To me, it seems like White has been a bit slow, which is why we can try the move g6, which is more ambitious. Even Be7 is good.} g6 13. b4 Bg7 14. a4 O-O $11 {We are not worried that White can fix the structure with some a5 incoming because we have a strong play and we know where we are headed. Black has strong play in the center or on the king's side with moves such as f5. We are fine with White taking some space over the queen's side while preparing f5.}) 7... Nd7 8. Nbd2 Be7 9. h3 Bh5 10. g4 Bg6 11. Nf1 h5 12. g5 h4 13. Rg1 Bh5 14. N1d2 Nf8 15. Qb3 Rb8 16. c5 Ne6 17. g6 Qd7 18. cxd6 cxd6 19. Qd1 fxg6 20. Rc1 Rf8 21. Bb6 Nf4 22. Rc3 Nxh3 23. Rh1 Ng5 24. d4 exd4 25. Rd3 Qe6 26. Nxg5 Bxg5 27. Qc2 Ke7 28. Rxd4 Rbc8 29. Rc4 Ne5 30. Rc7+ Kf6 0-1

