{[%evp 0,116,19,21,21,24,23,15,15,1,3,-46,-20,-8,8,-25,-26,-28,-19,-19,7,-29,-2,-2,17,-10,2,-7,2,-13,-10,-14,-21,-14,-24,-38,-32,-33,-38,-35,-38,-33,-51,-46,-39,-37,-55,-51,-40,-30,-30,-30,-34,-42,-32,-39,-36,-18,-21,-31,-32,-100,-88,-89,-80,-80,-92,-121,-93,-104,-98,-82,-76,-83,-83,-84,-96,-86,-45,-64,-61,-61,-56,-96,-87,-87,-97,-98,-79,-78,-78,-83,-83,-83,-83,-83,-83,-83,-83,-83,-83,-209,-217,-209,-10,-488,-598,-642,-732,-732,-830,-972,-1009,-1011,-1012,-1012,-1012,-1012,-1022] a great game by black ...in the line with 5.Bxc6} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. Bxc6 dxc6 6. d3 Bd6 (6... Bc5 {The bishop is misplaced on c5.} 7. Nxe5 (7. Nbd2) 7... Qd4 8. Be3 Qxe5 9. d4 Qxe4 10. dxc5 Qxg2 11. Rf1 Bh3) 7. Nbd2 Be6 (7... Bg4 8. h3 Bxf3 9. Nxf3 $14 {A position we should strictly avoid. We shouldn't give up our advantage by taking on f3. White has a small advantage now because many types of endgames will be better for him because he has much better-placed minor pieces.}) 8. h3 (8. Ng5 Bg4 9. f3 Bd7 $15) 8... Nd7 (8... Qd7 9. Ng5 $14 {We said we shouldn't give up the bishop like that.}) 9. b3 {With the idea to play Nc4.} b5 {Simply stopping Nc4 and changing the idea, now Black will go for a short castle.} 10. Nf1 f6 (10... O-O 11. Ng5 Bb4+ 12. Bd2 $17) 11. Ne3 c5 {Black is preparing to maneuver his knight to one of the magic squares - c6, e6, or g6.} 12. h4 h5 13. Nf5 Bf8 {Of course not giving up the bishop!} 14. Nd2 g6 15. Ne3 Nb8 16. a4 Nc6 17. Bb2 Bh6 18. O-O O-O $15 {Black plans to play good waiting moves and, at some point, to push either f5 or g5.} 19. Re1 Nd4 20. c3 Nc6 21. axb5 axb5 22. Rxa8 Qxa8 23. Qc2 Qd8 24. Nf3 Bg4 25. Nh2 Be6 26. Ra1 Qd7 27. Ra6 Rd8 28. Nhf1 Kf7 29. Ba3 Bf8 30. c4 Nb8 31. Ra8 Nc6 32. Rxd8 Qxd8 33. cxb5 Nd4 34. Qb1 Nxb5 35. Bb2 Nd4 36. Bxd4 cxd4 37. Nc4 Qa8 38. Qb2 Bb4 39. f4 exf4 40. Qxd4 Qf8 41. Qf2 Bxc4 42. bxc4 Qd6 43. Qf3 Be1 44. g3 Bxg3 45. Nxg3 fxg3 46. Kg2 c5 47. Qe3 Kg7 48. Qf3 Qe5 49. Kh3 Kf7 50. Qe3 g5 51. hxg5 Qxg5 52. Qxg3 Qxg3+ 53. Kxg3 Ke6 54. Kf4 h4 55. Kg4 Ke5 56. Kxh4 Kd4 57. Kg4 Kxd3 58. Kf5 Kd4 0-1

