{[%evp 0,165,21,23,23,17,22,25,18,-5,-8,6,4,11,14,8,26,30,34,29,35,6,19,-17,-19,-3,-13,-9,-9,-6,0,12,16,22,18,18,31,30,28,32,40,40,42,51,44,0,0,0,19,5,40,70,70,65,101,131,119,118,118,115,127,121,118,131,155,42,172,162,175,173,182,23,186,186,188,163,206,100,79,80,79,79,81,70,81,71,94,103,95,78,89,95,87,83,86,98,108,123,126,120,120,120,125,132,132,123,133,131,133,116,129,115,108,94,92,84,92,55,55,55,43,43,59,64,66,67,75,81,75,75,73,63,75,64,64,0,0,0,88,28,28,0,0,0,24,16,16,16,16,16,16,0,16,0,16,0,0,0,0,24,0,0,0,0,0,0,0,0] VERY NICE TYPICAL PLAY BY WHITE IN THE Bxc6 position} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. Bxc6 dxc6 6. d3 Bc5 (6... Bd6 7. Nbd2 {The correct move. As we mentioned the bishop on c5 is a bit misplaced.} Be6 8. O-O Nd7 9. Nb3 Qe7 (9... f6) 10. Ng5 Bxb3 11. axb3 O-O-O $15) 7. Nbd2 Nd7 8. Nc4 O-O 9. O-O Re8 {Not a bad version but still, the bishop is not so good on c5.} 10. Kh1 Bf8 {Intending c5 and f6, but the plan is slow.} 11. Ng1 Nc5 12. f4 exf4 13. Bxf4 Be6 14. Ne3 f6 15. Nf3 {White has a very nice little advantage.} Bd6 16. Bxd6 Qxd6 17. Qe1 b6 18. Qh4 Nd7 19. d4 Nf8 20. e5 fxe5 21. dxe5 Qc5 22. Rae1 Ng6 23. Qh5 Nf4 24. Qg5 Nd5 25. Nf5 Bxf5 26. Qxf5 Qe7 27. c4 Rf8 28. Qe4 Nf4 29. Nd4 Ng6 30. e6 Rxf1+ 31. Rxf1 Rf8 32. Re1 c5 33. Nf5 Qf6 34. e7 Re8 35. h4 h5 36. Qd5+ Qf7 37. g3 b5 38. b3 Qxd5+ 39. cxd5 c4 40. bxc4 bxc4 41. Re6 Kf7 42. Rc6 Nxe7 43. Rxc7 Kf8 44. Ne3 Ng6 45. Nxc4 Ne5 46. d6 Nxc4 47. Rxc4 Re1+ 48. Kg2 Rd1 49. Rc6 a5 50. Kf3 Kf7 51. Ra6 a4 52. Kf4 Kf6 53. d7+ Kf7 54. Rxa4 Rxd7 55. Re4 Rd2 56. a3 Kf6 57. Re3 Rd4+ 58. Kf3 Kf5 59. Rc3 Ra4 60. Ke3 Kg4 61. Kd2 g6 62. Kc2 Ra8 63. Kb3 Rb8+ 64. Kc4 Ra8 65. Kd5 Ra6 66. Ke5 g5 67. Rc4+ Kxg3 68. hxg5 Rxa3 69. g6 Ra8 70. Kf5 Ra5+ 71. Kf6 h4 72. g7 Ra6+ 73. Kg5 Ra5+ 74. Kf6 Ra6+ 75. Ke5 Ra5+ 76. Ke6 Ra6+ 77. Kf7 Ra7+ 78. Kg6 Ra6+ 79. Kh7 Ra7 80. Ra4 Rb7 81. Kh8 Rb8+ 82. g8=R+ Rxg8+ 83. Kxg8 1/2-1/2

