{Very instructive game, highlighting Black's problems if he is not aware of the details of the 5.Nc3 variation. The best move against this tricky line is 5...Be7!, postponing b7-b5 for a couple of moves!!   I advise not to ignore those tricky, minor lines.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. Nc3 b5 $6 (5... Be7 $1) 6. Bb3 Be7 7. a4 Rb8 8. axb5 axb5 9. d3 d6 10. Nd5 O-O 11. c3 $16 Bb7 12. h4 Qd7 13. Nxf6+ Bxf6 14. Ng5 Nd8 15. Qh5 h6 16. Qg6 Bxg5 17. hxg5 Ne6 18. Bxe6 Qxe6 19. Qxe6 fxe6 20. gxh6 Ra8 21. Rxa8 Rxa8 22. hxg7 Kxg7 23. Kd1 b4 24. cxb4 Ra4 25. Bh6+ Kg8 26. Bd2 Ra1+ 27. Bc1 Ra4 28. Rh6 Bc8 29. Bd2 Kg7 30. Rh5 Ra1+ 31. Ke2 Ba6 32. Bc3 Rg1 33. Rh2 Kg6 34. Rh8 d5 35. exd5 1-0

