{a top level game in tha fast d4 variation !} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 O-O 8. d4 d6 9. c3 Bg4 10. d5 Na5 11. Bc2 c6 12. h3 Bxf3 $1 {This move is also good, and it is leading to some Najdorf that is perfectly good for Black.} 13. Qxf3 cxd5 14. exd5 Nc4 {A good, perfectly fine position for Black. The bishop on e7 seems weak, but that is not the case. In the long run, Black intends to play g6 which will neutralize the c2 bishop, and later try putting the bishop to g7 or g5.} 15. Nd2 Nb6 {A very common idea because the knight on d2 needs to move again.} 16. Nf1 Re8 {We don't take on d5 because we don't want to give White compensation.} 17. Ng3 g6 18. Bh6 Rc8 $2 (18... Nc4 $1 19. Rab1 Nd7 $132) 19. a4 $1 b4 20. a5 bxc3 21. axb6 cxb2 22. Rxa6 Rxc2 23. Qb3 Qc8 24. b7 Qc3 25. Qxc3 Rxc3 26. Rb6 Rb8 27. Rxb2 Nxd5 28. Ra1 Bd8 29. Ra8 Bc7 30. Bd2 1-0

