1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 O-O 9. h3 Na5 10. Bc2 c5 11. d4 Qc7 12. Nbd2 Bd7 13. Nf1 Rfe8 14. dxe5 {A bad decision.} dxe5 15. N3h2 Rad8 16. Qf3 Be6 {White is somehow trying to maneuver his pieces, but Black has a very easy play.} 17. Ne3 Nc4 18. Nf5 Bxf5 {Often in Spanish, in close positions like that, we can give our bishop for the knight. I repeat, we do that ONLY if the position is closed!} 19. exf5 e4 20. Qe2 Bd6 21. Ng4 Nd5 22. f6 h5 23. Ne3 Ndxe3 24. Bxe3 Nxe3 25. fxe3 g6 26. a4 c4 27. axb5 axb5 28. Rad1 Qc5 29. Rf1 Qg5 30. Rd4 Qg3 31. Rxe4 Qh2+ 32. Kf2 Bg3+ 33. Kf3 Be5 34. Qf2 Re6 35. Rxe5 Qxe5 36. Ke2 Red6 0-1

