1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 O-O 8. c3 d6 9. h3 Na5 10. Bc2 c5 11. d4 Qc7 12. Nbd2 Bd7 13. Nf1 Rfe8 14. Ne3 g6 $5 {Playable and interesting.} 15. b3 {After b3 we quite often have to take on d4. The reason is that White has weakened some squares.} Bf8 16. Bb2 Rad8 (16... Bg7 17. d5 Nb7 18. Qd2 c4 19. b4 (19. bxc4 Nc5 $44) 19... a5 20. a3 Bh6 $15) 17. Nd2 Bg7 18. Qf3 (18. d5 $1 Bh6 19. c4 Nh5 $14) 18... cxd4 19. cxd4 Nc6 20. d5 Nd4 $15 21. Qd1 Nxc2 22. Nxc2 Rc8 23. Nb4 Qb6 24. Nd3 Bh6 25. Nf3 a5 26. Bc1 Bxc1 27. Rxc1 b4 28. Nb2 Bb5 29. g4 Rc3 30. Nd2 Rg3+ 0-1

