1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. O-O Be7 6. Re1 b5 7. Bb3 d6 8. c3 O-O 9. h3 Na5 10. Bc2 c5 11. d4 Qc7 12. Nbd2 Bd7 13. Nf1 Rfe8 14. b3 $5 {Let's repeat the rule: When we see b3 in this type of position we take on d4.} cxd4 $1 15. cxd4 Rac8 16. Ne3 Nc6 {Last opportunity to play Nc6, so we shouldn't miss it! If we do, White gets a better position.} 17. Bb2 (17. d5 $2 Nb4 18. Bb1 a5 19. Bd2 Na6 $132 {[%cal Ya6c5,Ye7d8,Yc7b7]}) 17... Bf8 $1 18. Rc1 Qd8 $1 19. d5 Nb4 20. Bb1 a5 21. Rxc8 Bxc8 22. Qe2 Qb6 23. Nf1 Na6 24. Bc1 Nc5 25. g4 Nfd7 26. Be3 Ba6 27. Ng3 b4 28. Qd2 Ra8 29. g5 Qb5 30. Bc2 a4 31. Nh2 Qa5 32. Ng4 axb3 33. axb3 Qa2 34. Qd1 g6 35. Kh2 Bg7 36. h4 Bb5 37. h5 Kf8 38. hxg6 hxg6 39. Ne2 Bxe2 40. Rxe2 Kg8 41. Kg2 Qb2 42. Qd2 1/2-1/2

